<br>
I now have a level 30 druid and I am so SICK of being everyones walking vending machine I could scream at times.<br>
<br>
I was in Freeport tonight minding my own business practing brewing and within about an hour. half the damn zone had sent me tells much like this:<br>
<br>
    Buff me plz<br>
    SoW me plz<br>
    I need a port<br>
<br>
One conversation went like this:<br>
<br>
Newbie:  Can you help me plz?<br>
Me:  What do you need?<br>
Newbie:  Take me to Kaladim<br>
Me:  Why don't you just go to EFP and take the boat?<br>
Newbie:  You can just zap me over there<br>
Me:  Sorry I'm working on trade skills right now I'm busy<br>
Newbie: Plz<br>
<br>
Finally I said ooc &quot;Can a woman do trade skills in peace without being accosted by every Tom, Dick, and Harry for sow, buffs, ports, and hand outs???&quot;<br>
<br>
I was in G-fay one day and announced porting for donations and this newb sent me a tell asking for a port to Butcherblock!  I asked him why he just didn't walk there and he complained about it taking to long he wanted ME to port him there and then when I did it he ran off stiffing me on the bill.<br>
<br>
Excuse my language but WTF!!!<br>
What is it with these damned newbs?  When I was a newb, I didn't even THINK about getting a port unless I was trying to get from NK to WC or visa versa.  I walked my bum off. These people want you to port them to WC from FP for nothing.  Oh yes, I'll port you, spend my time zoning and running all the way back to the city for jack squat.  Now don't get me wrong, I will port for free for those genuinely in need like a true newb who offers me 2pp because that's the best he can do for for a CR if I'm free, but I'll be damned if I will port their sorry arse 2 or even 1 zone away just so I can spend my time running back.<br>
<br>
And lastly, ever since I hit mid 20s on my druid, I must get anywhere from one to five tells a day begging me for items/money.  I have a 30 cleric that rarely gets beggers.  What is it about a druid that makes people think we're here to twink the hell out of them? <br>
<br>
Newb:  I'm a poor lv 1 can u plz give me stuff<br>
Me:  Oh sure, here take the 1k pp I have in the bank that I spent months working to save up, and while you're at it let me take the shirt off my back.  This PBB is nice, here, take it.  Do you see anything else you want?<br>
<br>
Again I have no problem with helping a newb who is actually trying to earn their way but I'd rather pour salt in an open wound then give a begger a single copper.  What I really want to do is get some of those ports to places like GD and Skyfire and port those beggers there and leave them to the fury of the mobs. <br>
<br>
Well I'm done ranting I realize this was long but I've finally reached my breaking point.  When someone walks up directly in my face and gives me &quot;the look of sow/buff/port me&quot; I just cringe inside.  Not all the time, but quite often because they're usually asking while i'm grouped, doing my business at the bank, running through town, getting my corpse, etc etc etc.<br>
<br>
The beggars have forced me into annonymity so it's back underground before they catch me here.  <br>
<br>
Take care and I welcome responses!<br>
<br>
Shaladarra Sowstorm (30 druid)<br>
Gabriarra Mistmoon (30 cleric) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uknightward.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KnightWard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/19/01 11:09:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbs who want a port to one zone away!! (Beggars too!)</span><hr size=1> Heh...<br>
<br>
I got my epic tonight..<br>
<br>
Right before the Fay battle I was asked for a port..<br>
<br>
I find taking the time to explain what your often helps.. but Not always, /ignore helps often in those cases.<br>
<br>
