<br>
The magic word is no. Just say no and get on with your business. You don't have an obligation to port them, if they say &quot;it's your job&quot; then ask them why you're not getting a paycheck.<br>
<br>
Also, &quot;porting for donations&quot; generally makes it sound like you'll port them no matter what. Donation makes people think paying for the port is optional. Better to advertise &quot;Porting for plat&quot; or &quot;Porting for a fee&quot; than to imply that payment is optional and get upset when someone doesn't pay for the service.<br>
<br>
Also, if the tells have gotten you that frustrated, /anon or /roleplay. They work wonders.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/userberus00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Serberus00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/21/01 4:25:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbs who want a port to one zone away...</span><hr size=1> i've had two druids to 45, one I refused to be anonymous simply because I didn't think it was really necessary, but the second I was trying to level as fast as possible and decided I could do without the tells for buffs n ports.<br>
<br>
Being anon has dropped my requests by about 90%, the only time anyone ever asks for a buff or a port is if they see me and realise i'm a druid, so the next step is to just buy a parrying dagger and be that dual wielding ranger. The fact that I run around in Wolfform most of the time doesn't really help hide my identity though, thats the beauty of hunting in completely obscure and out of the way places.<br>
<br>
I personally can't stand to be in any zone with newbie hunting grounds now simply because everyone who sees you begs for buffs.<br>
<br>
I'm happy to buff people who don't ask, i.e. someone hunting skeletons at the BB druid ring, but it annoys me intensely, especially when you get that newb who stands infront of you while your at the bank and you dread the next 10 seconds of your life just hoping that the nearest summoning mob decides he doesn't like you.<br>
<br>
Serberus <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessage?topicID=582.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessage?topicID=463.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.emailToFriend?topicID=579.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.threadControl?topicID=579.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=579.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=579.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm27">General - DAOC<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm18">FAQ & Index<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm20">Spoilers<option value="thedruidsgrovespells">Spells<option value="thedruidsgrovequests">Quests<option value="thedruidsgrovedruidicequipment">Druidic Equipment<option value="thedruidsgrovehuntingguide">Hunting Guide<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm25">PvP<option value="thedruidsgro